===  Delimiters and gaps

You can specify them the same way as for vectors.

Specify the arguments either before the content, or **after the semicolon** .
The code will panic if there is no semicolon!

    
    
    $
    mat(
        delim: "|",
        1, 2, ..., 10;
        2, 2, ..., 10;
        dots.v, dots.v, dots.down, dots.v;
        10, 10, ..., 10;
        gap: #0.3em
    )
    $

