> See [ official reference ](https://typst.app/docs/reference/math/mat/)

Matrix is very similar to ` vec  ` , but accepts rows, separated by ` ;  ` :

    
    
    $
    mat(
        1, 2, ..., 10;
        2, 2, ..., 10;
        dots.v, dots.v, dots.down, dots.v;
        10, 10, ..., 10; // `;` in the end is optional
